East 65th Street, west from Third Ave.

June 12, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(1) East 65th Street, west from a point midway between Third and Lexington Aves. and across the latter.

June 12, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(2) The same from a view point slightly westward and showing at the right foreground the building occupied by the Dominican Fathers. partially seen is the Parochial School of St. Vincent Ferrer, which is conducted by them.

June 12, 1937.

P. L. Sperr.

(3) Similar to No. 2 but showing only the north side. The 5-story corner building that appears prominently is No. 135, (also 868 Lexington Ave.). Adjacent to same appear two 4-story Lexington Ave. buildings. They are Nos. 872 and 874.
